items.text: Chicken Pesto salad was good and a decent size. Nice place ☺️
Great for sandwiches on weekdays, weekend menu was over priced and not upto their usual standards!
They do double shots here for their coffee. A bit on the bitter side for my taste buds but thankfully no sour aftertaste. Not my fav but definitely not bad.
Great sandwiches and salad for lunch and even better bites for dinner. Great coffe to complement it
Yummiest chicken pesto salad!
The brownie is so good. Only for the sweet toothed.
Big sandwiches and salads!
Good breakfast ☺
The usual bacon egg roll lacked punch. Bacon came in shredded pieces. Plus BBQ sauce wasn't a great match
Come here for the coffees & breakfast food. Yum!
Something smells good
Gorgeous Pesto here. I want it in my sandwiches n my salad! Will be back to try their breakfast. Scrambled eggs yumm. #ThomtoriEats
Great coffee. Cool place.
Suprisingly good espresso martinis
Had the smoked salmon sandwich. Good for an easy quick grab.
Coffee. Weekend brunch menu. Brownie.👌
Flat white and chicken pesto salad is a hit! Love it.
Ethiopian bean espresso is a rare treat and their rotating menu options are worth stopping in to check out. Go here instead of the nearby Starbucks.
Came for breakfast on a Saturday. Great relaxed vibe.... Wonderful salmon bagel (but a bit pricey at $16).... Staff here are excellent too.
Try to sit inside. The wind causes everything to fly away, including those delicious vegetables.
Really great big salads with lots of meat. Better value than most other places at the same price.
Used to be awesome but now food standards have dropped a bit. Pastries only come in at 10am (I come in at 9.15 and miss out) and not sure whether I ate more oil than goulash in the beef goulash.
Try the breakfast wrap. Great value.
Everything is huge.
Almond shake with Chia seeds- how I imagine all milk shakes should taste! Bacon- very well fried and NOT oily, very crispy! Granola wonderful crunch and taste w fresh fruits. DO NOT GET COCONUT WATER
Nice small café. We had a tasty breakfast (pancakes with fruits and Greek yoghurt) with quiet good coffee there. The service maybe not 100% professional, but the friendliness makes up for that.
Cocowhip: really weird. Doesn't taste of anything (even the matcha had no particular taste), not even coconut, and has too much air giving it a weird texture. Even stranger with salted caramel sauce
Paleo breakfast is the breakfast of champions!!!
A bit pricey, overall food was good. Must to try their hit mocha was super awesome
Awesome value from pimp my breakfast - sourdough, poached eggs, and salmon ftw!
Always crowded af, too tiny space. Superb love the intensity from iced mocha and brownies! I did not like their ice cream though.
Chicken pesto salad is refreshingly light yet filling.
The best bacon in Singapore!
The best piccolo in Singapore! Their home-baked salmon bagel is to die for!
Steak salad is very generous on the (very well cooked) steak
Chicken pesto sandwich is dry and tasteless. The bread they use is thick and distracting. Smoked salmon& potato salad is too salty and too much dressing, plus lots of onion. Why onion on a work day?
Amazing, quality Aussie-style coffee. Great fresh food (somewhat expensive), Aussie beers and friendly, down to earth staff. Love this place!!
Berry smoothie is absolutely tasteless!! Vanilla latte is good.
When churros are available, get them! Comes with chocolate, caramel and vanilla cream dips!
Place to come for a real sandwich - roast chicken with little bacon bits is a must.
Get anything with bacon ftw
Good place to meet for coffee or tea. Sit outside and watch the world go by.
The Schnitzel sandwich is missing something but I will give this shop another chance.
Coffe is great. Try ice long black, rich aroma and nice body
Herşey yenir 😃 mükemmel sandviç yapıyorlar
You have to try the weekend Sarnies, perfect bacon, amazing eggs and incredible relish. It's heaven.
Salad is yummy! Smoothies are a must!
Their sandwiches!
Sunday morning is not so crowded.., loved crispy breads and bacon..:)
The tandoori wrap was strictly okay. I will stick to the western options the next time.
The baked beans are to die for!
Dinner was good but they seriously screwed up our order. Lunch sandwich was okay - nothing special
Come here if u like lots and lots of bacon, and come here more often if you like to clog your poor arteries
Bitcoin accepted! Go for the Bullet Proof Coffee if you want something delicious & energizing. And you know how you never get enough bacon with breakfast? They give you enough. It's glorious.
The Mediterranean salad is good and comes with two generous chicken skewers. Expensive though.
Try the Soy Strawberries Cream Frappuccino - The only drink with the name "Soy" that I'd drink. :D
Good brunch place. Coffee is good too
Nice and healthy place. Lots of beverage options, as well as breakfast/brunch one's. Most importantly - open on Sunday
The weekend bacon & egg Sarnies is amazing. Love this place!
Pulled pork taco!!!!!
Generra (orange mocha) is amazing. If you are ok with soy milk, ask for that in place of regular... prepare for a magical, chocolaty explosion.
thought this place was tad overrated. service was friendly but it took 40 mins to prep our food. not to mention it was so crowded, with not enough seats, and was pricey- loved their mocha though
Cappuccino is good! And good place for work meetings
Great place with friendly staff. Don't be surprised to be greeted by your name if you go there often. Great sandwiches & also liked the Chicken Caesar Salad. Bottled beer @ $10 ain't bad for the CBD.
Piccolo here is great balance between coffee and not to much milk.
The wifi password is ilovebacon
Best coffee in town. Cool place, great food. Busy on a public holiday, tells you a lot.
The roast chicken sandwich is delicious, as is the steak sandwich. If you come on an evening try their chicken enchilada washed down with a Little Kreacher or 2...
Great for breakfast meetings... Strangely full at 9-10am during the work week...
Roast chicken Sandwich. lots of home cured bacon!
Ultra chilled place with awesome people and positive vibes. They put out the tables every wed-fri. Perfect for post-work drinks smack bang in the heart of the cbd.
Although just went for juice and wifi, the staff are really friendly and the place is cozy with fast internet!
Brilliant food great staff. Must visit !
Sometimes, the latte is just really that good. But the real catch is their hoagies - called toasties in these parts. Super. Awesome.
No matter how good the coffee is, a 15 minute wait is ridiculous!
Definitely one of the best coffee's I've had, and the music is great! Would love to try that place at night.
Decent selection of salads and sandwiches for lunch
Awesome brownies 😻
My long black was undrinkable. The place has a lively atmosphere though. Good for hanging out. Just come pre-caffeinated.
Oily... Extremely oily stuff. Good coffee though.
Not bad. But not great.
The cocowhip vegan ice cream is really good 😊
Best breakfast in Singapore. Try the beans, and the bacon, and the coffee!
Try the orange + cinnamon iced tea... It is exceptional!
Smoked salmon and scrambled eggs was the bomb!!! Great coffee too. One of my top brekkie places in Singapore.
Sister cafe to the Lokal, some repeated items in the menu, but overall an equally good cafe with great food and coffee.They make their own bagel, delicious with salmon & cream cheese.
Fry-Up: amazing bacon but the sausage was very underwhelming. Excellent home-made granola with berries, honey, and Greek yogurt. The latte tastes better than the flat white!
Amazing evening food, stumbled upon this place by accident and definitely didn't regret it. Try the Swedish meatballs!
Awesome coffee
Mocha / Iced Chocolate / Hummus Sandwich / Steak Salad. Best to avoid peak hours between 12-2pm.
Weekend brunch is a different menu from the weekday menus. The home cured bacon is da bomb!
Cosy spot (read: small) for brunch. The sandwiches are great.
password 12feb2014 : ilovebacon
Good street view. Enjoyed the outdoor seat. The bacon and egg sandwich I had is quite dry. Won't recommend for people like me who want a light nice breakfast with veggies. Latte is heavy but nice.
My husband surprised me with their Chicken in a Bag. Let's just say the marriage was worth it.
Roast chicken sandwich: Tried & loved it. Flavourful shreds of tasty chicken meat, crunchy bacon bits, avocado slices & guess what, sprinkles of cumin! Nice happy feeling in mouth :-D
Nice coffee!
Weekender Sarnies w mocha ❤️
The coconut water is bad... Stick to the coffee!
Good food reasonable price. Lovely!
Good food :)
Smoothies are great. Better after 930am crazy busy in the am.
Great option for healthy eating!! Check out the U-Fit menu!! Excellent coffee too😊
Food isn't great
Popular and famous for a reason. Good coffee, gi-fuckin-gantic sandwiches, hipster vibe without being asshats. The consistent anchor for Telok Ayer.
Great brunch and rye bread! I also love the staff and good coffee!
Green lemon & ginger tea: Ordered this & was pleasantly surprised when it was served. Instead of some teabag, it was a potful of fresh tea leave mixture. Impressed!
Mocha is really good.
Tacos!!!!!!
Great sandwiches, coffee and California ambience -:)
Get in before 11am to catch the breakfast menu. You don't want to miss out on trying their granola.
The almond milk/banana/berries/chia seeds smoothie: extremely tasty & refreshing! The brownie is a MUST-TRY: perfectly crispy on the outside & smooth & chocolatey on the inside
Pretty good toasted sandwiches made fresh
Cute setup - lovely smell throughout the place. Coffee nice. A bit noisy inside but adds to an atmosphere!?
Portion is gigantic! Love the granola and almond milk, banana, berries smoothie (vegan!) The fry up breakfast is good too and latte is really nice! Thumbs up guys!
Ethiopia cherry - the coffee in Spore!
A cosy cafe and have free wifi. But try to avoid to come during weekdays lunch hr, it can be quite hectic.
Order the Roast Chicken on Rye. Awesome
Breakfast: They serve bfast Mon-Fri 7:30am-11am. Not an extensive menu but just as tantalising! Salmon/bacon-egg bagel, scrambled eggs, BLT sandwich... Sounds good enuf 4 morning meet-ups in CBD :-)
The do a good salad with chunky pieces of chicken but definitely good for the brunch crowd & Sarnies of course!
Location: Hard to spot cafe w its black shade out, coverg sign. It's next 2 Fragrance Food kopitiam, cnr of Telok Ayer St & Boon Tat St. Park ard mosque & walk. There r wooden chairs & tables outside
The higher-than-average prices are well justified by quality and quantity of food.
